body_text.text:
To validate this new methodology, two time points were chosen for analysis: day 6 post-infection as this represents the peak of the viraemia and also day 14 as this represents a stage when virus isolation indicates all animals to be virus free. BVDV viral RNA was detected in whole blood taken at days 6 and 14 post-challenge in every calf (Fig. 3
). The estimates for viral genome copy number ranged from 1.95 × 105 to 5.88 × 105, and 1.92 × 105 to 3.22 × 105
 5′-UTR copies/ml blood on days 6 and 14, respectively.
